  "prompt": "What are 13.1 and 26.2 stickers and what do they mean?",
  "response": "The \"13.1\" and \"26.2\" stickers are commonly seen on vehicles, water bottles, or other personal items, and they represent significant milestones in running. Here's what they mean:\n\n- **13.1**: This number signifies the completion of a **half marathon**, which is a race that covers a distance of **13.1 miles** (or 21.1 kilometers). For many runners, finishing a half marathon is a major accomplishment and a stepping stone to longer distances.\n\n- **26.2**: This number represents the completion of a **full marathon**, a race that covers **26.2 miles** (or 42.2 kilometers). Completing a marathon is a significant achievement in the running community, often requiring months of dedicated training and perseverance.\n\nThese stickers are a way for runners to proudly display their accomplishments and share their passion for running with others.",
